The conference was delayed by a week to accommodate more branches. Courtesy of #DStv403 DURBAN - The ANC in KwaZulu-Natal is anticipating a dispute-free conference. It said the conference was delayed by a week to accommodate more branches. READ: KZN ANC gears up for elective conference It hopes all disputes have been resolved as the meeting gets underway on Friday. "We are not anticipating problems. The conference was supposed to take place last week," KZN ANC provincial secretary Mdumiseni Ntuli said. "We wanted to accommodate more branches. We didn’t want the conference to be filled with problems and complaints or disputes. In order to convene the conference."